# Rechecking Markdown Files

The user frequently edits markdown files between turns. When the user asks you
to "recheck", "re-read", "look again", or otherwise re-evaluate a markdown file:

- ALWAYS reload the file from disk using the Read tool before responding.
- NEVER rely on previously cached or remembered contents of the file.
- Treat any earlier version you saw in this conversation as stale.

This guarantees you are working against the user's latest edits.
